Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at Oglebay Resort and Conference Center in Wheeling, West Virginia, where he praised President Donald Trump and highlighted the administration's achievements. Pence emphasized the progress made in rebuilding the military, supporting law enforcement, and enforcing immigration laws. He also mentioned the tax cuts, deregulation, and the strong economy. Pence criticized Senator Joe Manchin for not supporting the President's agenda and encouraged the audience to support conservative leaders like West Virginia Attorney General Patrick Morrisey. He concluded by expressing his confidence in the future of America and urging the audience to pray for the nation.